id: pm-k1e4
title: "Extension activation: no teardown/deactivation hook — extensions cannot clean up timers, connections, or state"
description: "Extensions can register hooks and overrides during activate(api), but there is no corresponding deactivate() or onTeardown() lifecycle. An extension that opens a database connection, starts a timer, or allocates a buffer at activation has no way to clean up when the CLI process exits or when 'pm extension reload' is called. This matters most for: (1) packages running long search-index connections (pm-search-advanced with an external vector store), (2) lifecycle-hooks that hold open log sinks, (3) reload scenarios in MCP where extensions are re-loaded per request. An optional `deactivate(): Promise<void> | void` export on the extension module (analogous to VS Code's deactivate export) would close this gap."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 3
tags[4]: "area:extensions","area:sdk",extensibility,lifecycle
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:05:20.632Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-07T17:04:46.205Z"
author: audit-platform-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- Extension API supports a deactivate/teardown lifecycle hook invoked on shutdown/reload\n- Long-running MCP server invokes teardown on extension reload\n- Covered by tests; lifecycle documented"
parent: pm-ugqx
risk: medium
confidence: medium
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-07T17:04:46.205Z",maintainer-agent,"Audit 2026-06-07 (SDK agent F5): pair the missing teardown/deactivation hook with a missing hooks.onError(context) — ExtensionApi.hooks only exposes before/after/onWrite/onRead/onIndex, so extensions can neither clean up on abort nor observe failures. Consider api.onTeardown(fn) / module deactivate(api) + hooks.onError together."
body: ""
